com.cyc.base.kbtool

Interface AssertTool

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CycAssertTool

    public interface AssertTool
    Tools for asserting facts to the Cyc KB. To unassert facts from the Cyc KB, use the UnassertTool. To perform simple tasks, like constant creation or renaming, use the ObjectTool.
    See Also:
    UnassertTool, ObjectTool

      • edit

        void edit(String unassertSentence,
        String assertSentence,
        ElMt mt,
        boolean bookkeeping,
        boolean transcript,
        boolean disableWFFChecking,
        List<Fort> templates)
          throws CycApiException,
                 CycConnectionException
        Edit the sentence contained in unassertSentence to instead be assertSentence. If the Mt is null, unassertSentence and assertSentence must be contextualized sentences (i.e. the Mt must be specified using #$ist). If unassertSentence is an empty conjunction, this amounts to "assert", while if assertSentence is an empty conjunction, it amounts to unassert. This is transactional--if the edit can't be carried out, the old assertion is left in place and a CycAPIException is thrown.
        Parameters:
        unassertSentence -
        assertSentence -
        mt -
        bookkeeping -
        transcript -
        disableWFFChecking -
        templates -
        Throws:
        CycConnectionException
        CycApiException
